{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I think it'll be a relief to some people and a disappointment to others"},{"time":3000,"text":"that I'm not going to talk about vaginas today."},{"time":6000,"text":"I began \"The Vagina Monologues\" because I was worried about vaginas."},{"time":11000,"text":"I'm very worried today about this notion, this world,"},{"time":15000,"text":"this prevailing kind of force of security."},{"time":19000,"text":"I see this word, hear this word, feel this word everywhere."},{"time":23000,"text":"Real security, security checks, security watch, security clearance."},{"time":26000,"text":"Why has all this focus on security made me feel so much more insecure?"},{"time":32000,"text":"What does anyone mean when they talk about real security?"},{"time":36000,"text":"And why have we, as Americans particularly,"},{"time":38000,"text":"become a nation that strives for security above all else?"},{"time":42000,"text":"In fact, I think that security is elusive. It's impossible."},{"time":46000,"text":"We all die. We all get old. We all get sick. People leave us."},{"time":50000,"text":"People change us. Nothing is secure."},{"time":52000,"text":"And that's actually the good news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55000,"text":"This is, of course, unless your whole life is about being secure."},{"time":59000,"text":"I think that when that is the focus of your life,"},{"time":62000,"text":"these are the things that happen."},{"time":64000,"text":"You can't travel very far or venture too far outside a certain circle."},{"time":69000,"text":"You can't allow too many conflicting ideas into your mind at one time,"},{"time":73000,"text":"as they might confuse you or challenge you."},{"time":76000,"text":"You can't open yourself to new experiences, new people,"},{"time":79000,"text":"new ways of doing things -- they might take you off course."},{"time":82000,"text":"You can't not know who you are, so you cling to hard-matter identity."},{"time":87000,"text":"You become a Christian, Muslim, Jew."},{"time":89000,"text":"You're an Indian, Egyptian, Italian, American."},{"time":92000,"text":"You're a heterosexual or a homosexual, or you never have sex."},{"time":95000,"text":"Or at least, that's what you say when you identify yourself."},{"time":98000,"text":"You become part of an \"us.\""},{"time":100000,"text":"In order to be secure, you defend against \"them.\""},{"time":103000,"text":"You cling to your land because it is your secure place."},{"time":106000,"text":"You must fight anyone who encroaches upon it."},{"time":108000,"text":"You become your nation. You become your religion."},{"time":110000,"text":"You become whatever it is that will freeze you, numb you"},{"time":113000,"text":"and protect you from doubt or change."},{"time":116000,"text":"But all this does, actually, is shut down your mind."},{"time":120000,"text":"In reality, it does not really make you safer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123000,"text":"I was in Sri Lanka, for example, three days after the tsunami,"},{"time":127000,"text":"and I was standing on the beaches"},{"time":129000,"text":"and it was absolutely clear that, in a matter of five minutes,"},{"time":132000,"text":"a 30-foot wave could rise up"},{"time":134000,"text":"and desecrate a people, a population and lives."},{"time":137000,"text":"All this striving for security, in fact,"},{"time":140000,"text":"has made you much more insecure"},{"time":142000,"text":"because now you have to watch out all the time."},{"time":145000,"text":"There are people not like you -- people who you now call enemies."},{"time":148000,"text":"You have places you cannot go, thoughts you cannot think,"},{"time":151000,"text":"worlds that you can no longer inhabit."},{"time":153000,"text":"And so you spend your days fighting things off, defending your territory"},{"time":157000,"text":"and becoming more entrenched in your fundamental thinking."},{"time":160000,"text":"Your days become devoted to protecting yourself."},{"time":163000,"text":"This becomes your mission. That is all you do."},{"time":166000,"text":"Ideas get shorter. They become sound bytes."},{"time":169000,"text":"There are evildoers and saints, criminals and victims."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172000,"text":"There are those who, if they're not with us, are against us."},{"time":175000,"text":"It gets easier to hurt people because you do not feel what's inside them."},{"time":178000,"text":"It gets easier to lock them up, force them to be naked, humiliate them,"},{"time":182000,"text":"occupy them, invade them and kill them,"},{"time":184000,"text":"because they are only obstacles now to your security."},{"time":188000,"text":"In six years, I've had the extraordinary privilege through V-Day,"},{"time":192000,"text":"a global movement against [violence against] women,"},{"time":193000,"text":"to travel probably to 60 countries,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and spend a great deal of time in different portions."},{"time":200000,"text":"I've met women and men all over this planet,"},{"time":203000,"text":"who through various circumstances --"},{"time":205000,"text":"war, poverty, racism, multiple forms of violence --"},{"time":209000,"text":"have never known security,"},{"time":211000,"text":"or have had their illusion of security forever devastated."},{"time":215000,"text":"I've spent time with women in Afghanistan under the Taliban,"},{"time":218000,"text":"who were essentially brutalized and censored."},{"time":221000,"text":"I've been in Bosnian refugee camps."},{"time":223000,"text":"I was with women in Pakistan"},{"time":225000,"text":"who have had their faces melted off with acid."},{"time":228000,"text":"I've been with girls all across America who were date-raped,"},{"time":231000,"text":"or raped by their best friends when they were drugged one night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"One of the amazing things that I've discovered in my travels"},{"time":238000,"text":"is that there is this emerging species."},{"time":240000,"text":"I loved when he was talking about this other world that's right next to this world."},{"time":244000,"text":"I've discovered these people, who, in V-Day world,"},{"time":247000,"text":"we call Vagina Warriors."},{"time":249000,"text":"These particular people, rather than getting AK-47s,"},{"time":253000,"text":"or weapons of mass destruction, or machetes,"},{"time":256000,"text":"in the spirit of the warrior, have gone into the center, the heart of pain, of loss."},{"time":261000,"text":"They have grieved it, they have died into it,"},{"time":264000,"text":"and allowed and encouraged poison to turn into medicine."},{"time":268000,"text":"They have used the fuel of their pain to begin to redirect that energy"},{"time":272000,"text":"towards another mission and another trajectory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275000,"text":"These warriors now devote themselves and their lives"},{"time":278000,"text":"to making sure what happened to them doesn't happen to anyone else."},{"time":282000,"text":"There are thousands if not millions of them on the planet."},{"time":285000,"text":"I venture there are many in this room."},{"time":287000,"text":"They have a fierceness and a freedom"},{"time":289000,"text":"that I believe is the bedrock of a new paradigm."},{"time":292000,"text":"They have broken out of the existing frame of victim and perpetrator."},{"time":297000,"text":"Their own personal security is not their end goal,"},{"time":300000,"text":"and because of that, because, rather than worrying about security,"},{"time":304000,"text":"because the transformation of suffering is their end goal,"},{"time":307000,"text":"I actually believe they are creating real safety"},{"time":310000,"text":"and a whole new idea of security."},{"time":313000,"text":"I want to talk about a few of these people that I've met."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316000,"text":"Tomorrow, I am going to Cairo,"},{"time":318000,"text":"and I'm so moved that I will be with women in Cairo"},{"time":322000,"text":"who are V-Day women, who are opening the first safe house"},{"time":325000,"text":"for battered women in the Middle East."},{"time":327000,"text":"That will happen because women in Cairo made a decision to stand up"},{"time":331000,"text":"and put themselves on the line,"},{"time":333000,"text":"and talk about the degree of violence that is happening in Egypt,"},{"time":336000,"text":"and were willing to be attacked and criticized."},{"time":340000,"text":"And through their work over the last years,"},{"time":343000,"text":"this is not only happening that this house is opening,"},{"time":345000,"text":"but it's being supported by many factions of the society"},{"time":348000,"text":"who never would have supported it."},{"time":350000,"text":"Women in Uganda this year,"},{"time":352000,"text":"who put on \"The Vagina Monologues\" during V-Day,"},{"time":355000,"text":"actually evoked the wrath of the government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"And, I love this story so much."},{"time":360000,"text":"There was a cabinet meeting and a meeting of the presidents"},{"time":363000,"text":"to talk about whether \"Vaginas\" could come to Uganda."},{"time":366000,"text":"And in this meeting -- it went on for weeks in the press,"},{"time":369000,"text":"two weeks where there was huge discussion."},{"time":371000,"text":"The government finally made a decision"},{"time":373000,"text":"that \"The Vagina Monologues\" could not be performed in Uganda."},{"time":376000,"text":"But the amazing news was that because they had stood up, these women,"},{"time":380000,"text":"and because they had been willing to risk their security,"},{"time":383000,"text":"it began a discussion that not only happened in Uganda,"},{"time":386000,"text":"but all of Africa."},{"time":388000,"text":"As a result, this production, which had already sold out,"},{"time":391000,"text":"every single person in that 800-seat audience, except for 10 people,"},{"time":396000,"text":"made a decision to keep the money."},{"time":399000,"text":"They raised 10,000 dollars on a production that never occurred."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404000,"text":"There's a young woman named Carrie Rethlefsen in Minnesota."},{"time":407000,"text":"She's a high school student."},{"time":409000,"text":"She had seen \"The Vagina Monologues\" and she was really moved. And as a result,"},{"time":413000,"text":"she wore an \"I heart my vagina\" button to her high school in Minnesota."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"She was basically threatened to be expelled from school."},{"time":424000,"text":"They told her she couldn't love her vagina in high school,"},{"time":427000,"text":"that it was not a legal thing, that it was not a moral thing,"},{"time":430000,"text":"that it was not a good thing."},{"time":432000,"text":"So she really struggled with this, what to do,"},{"time":434000,"text":"because she was a senior and she was doing well in her school"},{"time":437000,"text":"and she was threatened expulsion. So what she did is she got all her friends together --"},{"time":441000,"text":"I believe it was 100, 150 students"},{"time":444000,"text":"all wore \"I love my vagina\" T-shirts,"},{"time":447000,"text":"and the boys wore \"I love her vagina\" T-shirts to school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452000,"text":"Now this seems like a fairly, you know, frivolous,"},{"time":455000,"text":"but what happened as a result of that, is that that school now"},{"time":460000,"text":"is forming a sex education class. It's beginning to talk about sex,"},{"time":464000,"text":"it's beginning to look at why it would be wrong"},{"time":467000,"text":"for a young high school girl to talk about her vagina publicly"},{"time":470000,"text":"or to say that she loved her vagina publicly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473000,"text":"I know I've talked about Agnes here before,"},{"time":476000,"text":"but I want to give you an update on Agnes."},{"time":478000,"text":"I met Agnes three years ago in the Rift Valley."},{"time":480000,"text":"When she was a young girl, she had been mutilated against her will."},{"time":486000,"text":"That mutilation of her clitoris"},{"time":488000,"text":"had actually obviously impacted her life"},{"time":490000,"text":"and changed it in a way that was devastating."},{"time":493000,"text":"She made a decision not to go and get a razor or a glass shard,"},{"time":497000,"text":"but to devote her life to stopping that happening to other girls."},{"time":501000,"text":"For eight years, she walked through the Rift Valley."},{"time":504000,"text":"She had this amazing box that she carried and it had a"},{"time":506000,"text":"torso of a woman's body in it, a half a torso,"},{"time":509000,"text":"and she would teach people, everywhere she went,"},{"time":511000,"text":"what a healthy vagina looked like and what a mutilated vagina looked like."},{"time":514000,"text":"In the years that she walked, she educated parents, mothers, fathers."},{"time":518000,"text":"She saved 1,500 girls from being cut."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"When V-Day met her, we asked her how we could support her"},{"time":523000,"text":"and she said, \"Well, if you got me a Jeep,"},{"time":525000,"text":"I could get around a lot faster.\" So, we bought her a Jeep."},{"time":528000,"text":"In the year she had the Jeep, she saved 4,500 girls from being cut."},{"time":533000,"text":"So, we said, what else could we do?"},{"time":534000,"text":"She said, \"If you help me get money, I could open a house.\""},{"time":537000,"text":"Three years ago, Agnes opened a safe house in Africa to stop mutilation."},{"time":544000,"text":"When she began her mission eight years ago, she was reviled,"},{"time":548000,"text":"she was detested, she was completely slandered in her community."},{"time":552000,"text":"I am proud to tell you that six months ago,"},{"time":555000,"text":"she was elected the deputy mayor of Narok."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":565000,"text":"I think what I'm trying to say here"},{"time":567000,"text":"is that if your end goal is security,"},{"time":571000,"text":"and if that's all you're focusing on, what ends up happening"},{"time":574000,"text":"is that you create not only more insecurity in other people,"},{"time":577000,"text":"but you make yourself far more insecure."},{"time":580000,"text":"Real security is contemplating death, not pretending it doesn't exist."},{"time":585000,"text":"Not running from loss, but entering grief, surrendering to sorrow."},{"time":590000,"text":"Real security is not knowing something, when you don't know it."},{"time":594000,"text":"Real security is hungering for connection rather than power."},{"time":598000,"text":"It cannot be bought or arranged or made with bombs."},{"time":601000,"text":"It is deeper, it is a process, it is acute awareness"},{"time":605000,"text":"that we are all utterly inter-bended,"},{"time":607000,"text":"and one action by one being in one tiny town"},{"time":610000,"text":"has consequences everywhere."},{"time":613000,"text":"Real security is not only being able"},{"time":615000,"text":"to tolerate mystery, complexity, ambiguity, but hungering for them"},{"time":619000,"text":"and only trusting a situation when they are present."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622000,"text":"Something happened when I began traveling in V-Day, eight years ago. I got lost."},{"time":628000,"text":"I remember being on a plane going from Kenya to South Africa,"},{"time":633000,"text":"and I had no idea where I was."},{"time":634000,"text":"I didn't know where I was going, where I'd come from,"},{"time":637000,"text":"and I panicked. I had a total anxiety attack."},{"time":640000,"text":"And then I suddenly realized that it absolutely didn't matter"},{"time":643000,"text":"where I was going, or where I had come from"},{"time":645000,"text":"because we are all essentially permanently displaced people."},{"time":650000,"text":"All of us are refugees."},{"time":652000,"text":"We come from somewhere and we are hopefully traveling all the time,"},{"time":655000,"text":"moving towards a new place."},{"time":657000,"text":"Freedom means I may not be identified as any one group,"},{"time":661000,"text":"but that I can visit and find myself in every group."},{"time":665000,"text":"It does not mean that I don't have values or beliefs,"},{"time":668000,"text":"but it does mean I am not hardened around them."},{"time":670000,"text":"I do not use them as weapons."},{"time":673000,"text":"In the shared future, it will be just that, shared."},{"time":678000,"text":"The end goal will [be] becoming vulnerable,"},{"time":680000,"text":"realizing the place of our connection to one another,"},{"time":683000,"text":"rather than becoming secure, in control and alone."},{"time":688000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":693000,"text":"Chris Anderson: And how are you doing? Are you exhausted?"},{"time":698000,"text":"On a typical day, do you wake up with hope or gloom?"},{"time":702000,"text":"Eve Ensler: You know, I think Carl Jung once said"},{"time":704000,"text":"that in order to survive the twentieth century,"},{"time":707000,"text":"we have to live with two existing thoughts, opposite thoughts, at the same time."},{"time":711000,"text":"And I think part of what I'm learning in this process"},{"time":715000,"text":"is that one must allow oneself to feel grief."},{"time":719000,"text":"And I think as long as I keep grieving, and weeping,"},{"time":722000,"text":"and then moving on, I'm fine."},{"time":724000,"text":"When I start to pretend that what I'm seeing isn't impacting me,"},{"time":728000,"text":"and isn't changing my heart, then I get in trouble."},{"time":732000,"text":"Because when you spend a lot of time going from place to place,"},{"time":736000,"text":"country to country, and city to city,"},{"time":738000,"text":"the degree to which women, for example, are violated,"},{"time":741000,"text":"and the epidemic of it, and the kind of ordinariness of it,"},{"time":745000,"text":"is so devastating to one's soul that you have to take the time,"},{"time":750000,"text":"or I have to take the time now, to process that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753000,"text":"CA: There are a lot of causes out there in the world that have been talked about,"},{"time":757000,"text":"you know, poverty, sickness and so on. You spent eight years on this one."},{"time":762000,"text":"Why this one?"},{"time":764000,"text":"EE: I think that if you think about women,"},{"time":766000,"text":"women are the primary resource of the planet. They give birth,"},{"time":771000,"text":"we come from them, they are mothers, they are visionaries,"},{"time":774000,"text":"they are the future. If you think that the U.N. now says"},{"time":777000,"text":"that one out of three women on the planet"},{"time":779000,"text":"will be raped or beaten in their lifetime,"},{"time":782000,"text":"we're talking about the desecration of the primary resource of the planet,"},{"time":786000,"text":"we're talking about the place where we come from, we're talking about parenting."},{"time":789000,"text":"Imagine that you've been raped and you're bringing up a boy child."},{"time":791000,"text":"How does it impact your ability to work, or envision a future,"},{"time":795000,"text":"or thrive, as opposed to just survive? What I believe is"},{"time":799000,"text":"if we could figure out how to make women safe and honor women,"},{"time":803000,"text":"it would be parallel or equal to honoring life itself."}]}]}